@startuml use-cases-data-lifecycle
title trawhile — Data Lifecycle (Epic 8)

note as N
  Epic 8 is fully automated — no UI interaction required.

  Retention periods and node retention are configured via
  the system config file (SR-F050.F05).

  Activity purge (SR-F050.F01/F02) runs nightly at 23:59
  (company timezone), deleting whatever crossed the rolling
  retention cutoff as of that night. Node deletion
  (SR-F050.F03/F04) runs immediately after each nightly
  activity purge. Both jobs are idempotent and resume on
  application restart using stored cutoff_date.

  Invitation auto-expiry (SR-C010.C01) runs daily,
  transitioning users with expired pending_invitations
  to the Ready for Scrubbing state (SR-F047.F02).

  See state-purge-lifecycle.puml for entity lifecycle states
  and cross-entity deletion dependencies.
end note

@enduml
